==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Goldsmith
<hw>Gold"smith`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. goldsmi<?/.
See <er>Gold</er>., and <er>Smith</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
artisan who manufactures vessels and ornaments, etc., of gold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A banker.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The goldsmiths of London formerly received money on
deposit because they were prepared to keep it safely.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Goldsmith beetle</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
large, bright yellow, American beetle (<spn>Cotalpa lanigera</spn>), of
the family <fam>Scarab⟦ae⟧id⟦ae⟧</fam></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goldtit</ent>⟦br⟧
